KAHN, Respondent, v. NEW YORK EL. R. CO., Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County,

General Term.

May 10, 1893.) Action by Herman Kahn against the New York Elevated Railroad Company.

Argued before DALY, C. J., and BOOKSTAVER, J.

Davies & Rapallo, for appellant. Wolff & Hodge, for respondent.

No opinion. Motion for reargument granted. See 22 N. Y. Supp. 793.
